			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: guild help<a name="54253"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 29 04 10:52 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Here are some ideas on possible guild progression. Its nothing original, and probably left some gaps that others will fill in<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Avg level 46-55: 
<br />
Kael arena. Work on faction and get some BPs/Legs in particular. Mostly its about getting non-KoS to Claws of Veeshan (CoV) faction though.
<br />

<br />
UP mini-names, Tawro and Radir. Drop the bracelets of XXX (sense, beauty, strength etc) and some decent weapons in particular.
<br />

<br />
PoFear/PoHate - for epic drops and learning basic raid discipline. Start with PoHate as CRs are quite easy these days - breaking in to fear can still cause problems for low level, inexperienced raiders but is well worth learning.
<br />

<br />
Avg level 55-65: 
<br />
Halls of Testing. Need to have decent CoV faction. Note that killing dragons in the halls of testing won't damage any faction.
<br />

<br />
The Hole - Guardian of the Seal. DA drop in from above and you can do this very quickly for some nice drops.
<br />

<br />
Encourage people to XP in the desert in PoStorms to get the quest access to Tactics from killing the Diaku there. Tactics is a great xp zone and also has some mini-named you can do.
<br />

<br />
Also look at the PoS giant-killing quests for access to BoT. If you can get enough people 55+ keyed for BoT then you can start BoT tower raids, which give out truly drool-worthy loot at that kind of level. If you don't do the quests you'll have to wait til level 62, and besides you need to do this eventually for PoP progression anyway.
<br />

<br />
Avg Level 60-65:
<br />
Once you are clearing HoT successfully, start working on Luclin and some PoP tier 1 content. Some mobs you can do even sooner. Good initial targets include:
<br />
Servitor of Luclin (easy) and Grieg (medium) in Grieg's End
<br />
Itraer Vius (easy-/medium) and Va'dynn (trivial) in Akheva
<br />
Zelni...., Doomshade (DS) and RumbleCrush (RC) in Umbral Planes.
<br />
Ssra - some of the easier named like XTC.
<br />
Mini PoP content. Hedge trial in PoN. PoI dragon (Xanamech), Vhaksiz the shade, BoT towers (BoT Towers are THE best source of good loot for small guilds imo - ornate BP patterns/molds, runes, and more!)
<br />

<br />
Once you are killing these fairly easy, move on to the tougher named in Ssra like Cursed, HP etc. Start thinking about taking a crack at the Avatar of War. Eventually move on to Emperor -&gt; VT Keys. If you are killing Cursed/HP then you can also do PoP gods such as TT, Grummus etc for some flags and more loot.
<br />

<br />
If you have a core of 6-12 people who are already 65 with some AAs then they can easily do the easier targets with some support from lower levels, which would allow you to move up the progression to the 60-65 content very fast - its just a case of getting people to learn to assist, learn to pull, learn the CH chains and so forth. If you don't have many 60+ with raid experiance then use Velious and the Old World planes as a training ground.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
