				<td colspan="2"><span>If you want to avoid becoming a feeder guild, you will need to instill your guild with some drive.  They need to know that they're going somewhere.  I would actually reccomend doing a wide variety of raid targets, starting with smaller stuff, and working your way up.  I'd reccomend starting with Kunark era stuff, and working your way up.
<br />

<br />
If you spend a long time farming the same old stuff, people will think that your guild is stagnant, and you will become a feeder guild.  If you keep showing them new content, they'll stick around.
<br />

<br />
I'm currently elemental flagged, and VT keyed, and I'm actually looking into doing more group-to-small raid content with Molto.  Big raids are great for gear, and it's always fun to take down big targets, but even the most uber of zones get stale. </span></td>
