				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Beginning raid suggestions<a name="54671"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 1 04 2:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm not a guild or raid leader, but I joined a family guild when I was about level 40.  We have a core of 65s and a goodly handful of 50-odds and below.  The raids we did that first taught me what to do (places I think would help you get everyone used to raiding) were primarily outdoor dragons (Gorenaire, Talendor) and epic raids (lots of Chardok).  The dragons, if you can catch them, are very easy to recover from since they wander off if you wipe.  For Chardok it helped to have a couple of people who've fought in Nurga and Droga enough to not be KoS to the sarnaks.  I think Kael was a good suggestion too - they're places you can use to learn.
<br />

<br />
Gear I have no comments on - I live off hand-me-downs from friends and occasional random drops.
<br />

<br />
Good luck with your new guild and I hope you enjoy yourself in the process of getting where you want to be.
<br />

